WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:03.564
"THE ELEPHANT TEACHER
SMILED AT THE ZEBRA.

00:03.564 --> 00:07.327
"'OF COURSE YOU CAN COME INTO
MY JUNGLE CLASSROOM,' SHE SAID.

00:07.327 --> 00:11.411
AND THAT'S HOW THE ZEBRA
LEARNED TO READ."

00:11.411 --> 00:15.295
ALL RIGHT.
YOUR WATER'S HERE.

00:15.295 --> 00:17.137
MR. BEAR'S WATER
IS HERE.

00:17.137 --> 00:20.901
YOUR CLOTHES ARE LAID OUT
FOR THE ENTIRE WEEK.

00:20.901 --> 00:23.063
NO JUDGEMENT ‐‐
MY LOVE IS UNCONDITIONAL.

00:23.063 --> 00:26.627
WHAT DO YOU SAY, LITTLE MAN?
SHOULD WE GO TO SLEEP?

00:26.627 --> 00:27.828
CAN I HAVE
ANOTHER FOOT RUB?

00:27.828 --> 00:29.790
[ BOTH GROAN ]
THAT'S ENOUGH STALLING.

00:29.790 --> 00:31.111
WHAT'S "STALLING"?

00:32.232 --> 00:34.474
UH...HOW DO YOU
EXPLAIN STALLING?

00:34.474 --> 00:35.796
HE KNOWS
WHAT STALLING IS.

00:35.796 --> 00:38.278
I FORGET AGAIN.

00:38.278 --> 00:41.041
LET'S CLOSE OUR EYES
AND GO TO SLEEP.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.923
I'M GONNA COUNT DOWN
FROM 10.

00:42.923 --> 00:45.325
OOH,
COUNT DOWN FROM 500.

00:47.207 --> 00:49.970
500...

00:49.970 --> 00:52.132
499...

00:52.132 --> 00:56.937
498...

00:56.937 --> 00:58.979
497...

01:11.151 --> 01:14.875
HE'S GETTING BETTER.
THAT WAS PRETTY QUICK.

01:14.875 --> 01:17.077
SWEETIE,
HE'S MADE YOU HIS BITCH.

01:17.077 --> 01:19.119
I'M PRETTY SURE
I DID IT TO MYSELF.

01:19.119 --> 01:22.442
HEY. FIRST ONE TO THE LIVING
ROOM GETS TO PICK THE SHOW.

01:26.607 --> 01:28.408
[ GASPS ]
HEY! STOP IT!

01:28.408 --> 01:30.130
NO. SHH!

01:31.171 --> 01:32.733
I THINK
I HEARD SOMETHING.

01:33.493 --> 01:34.494
SUCKER!

01:34.494 --> 01:39.179
HEY! THAT'S NOT FAIR!

01:39.179 --> 01:42.663
♪♪♪

01:49.309 --> 01:52.112
OKAY, WHOEVER EATS THEIR FRUIT
IS MY FAVORITE CHILD.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.714
THERE YOU GO, MAN.
UH, HEY, DAD.

01:53.714 --> 01:55.275
I HAVE A HANGNAIL.
CAN YOU, UM...

01:55.275 --> 01:56.917
OH, I'LL GET THE CLIPPERS.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

01:56.917 --> 01:58.198
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

01:58.198 --> 02:00.561
I GOT IT.
OKAY, ON THREE.

02:00.561 --> 02:03.123
ONE...TWO! OH!
AAH!

02:03.123 --> 02:04.845
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
MAKE IT TO THREE.

02:04.845 --> 02:05.886
YOU NEVER MAKE IT TO THREE.
I DIDN'T MAKE IT TO THREE.

02:05.886 --> 02:08.208
TWO'S...BEFORE THAT.

02:08.208 --> 02:11.211
OH, HEY. WHOSE, UH ‐‐
WHOSE FANCY HEADBAND'S THIS?

02:11.211 --> 02:13.293
THOSE ARE MINE.

02:13.293 --> 02:15.055
OH! RED THONG ‐‐
SO CLASSY.

02:15.055 --> 02:18.258
DAD, CAN YOU PLEASE
DO MY NECKLACE?
OH, I'LL DO IT.

02:18.258 --> 02:19.459
OH, I GOT IT.
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

02:19.459 --> 02:21.862
DAD, WHAT'S A THONG?

02:21.862 --> 02:23.664
OH, IT'S, UH, UNDERWEAR

02:23.664 --> 02:25.145
FOR PEOPLE WHO DON'T
WANT PANTY LINES.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.627
OH, WELL, WHY WOULDN'T YOU
WANT PANTY LINES?

02:26.627 --> 02:28.028
'CAUSE IT'S NOT SEXY.

02:28.028 --> 02:30.270
WHOO! SEXY TIME!

02:30.270 --> 02:31.552
'CAUSE YOU GUYS
LIKE TO HAVE ‐‐

02:31.552 --> 02:35.395
AND THUS ENDS OUR MORNING
UNDERWEAR Q AND A.

02:35.395 --> 02:37.758
RIGHT. YEP. OF COURSE.

02:37.758 --> 02:39.880
DAD, PLEASE JUST SIGN
MY PERMISSION SLIPS?
YEAH.

02:39.880 --> 02:41.081
OH, I CAN DO IT.
YES. I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

02:41.081 --> 02:42.442
YOU ARE NOT A PARENT.
I KNOW. MM‐HMM.

02:42.442 --> 02:44.404
WHEN YOU'RE DONE WITH THAT,
I‐I NEED FIVE BUCKS.

02:44.404 --> 02:45.405
FOR WHAT?

02:45.405 --> 02:47.047
FOR AN INVESTMENT.

02:47.047 --> 02:48.769
OH, CAN I WEAR MY ‐‐
AN INVESTMENT?

02:48.769 --> 02:50.370
CAN I WEAR MY SHIN GUARDS
TO SCHOOL?
WHAT ARE YOU INVESTING IN?

02:50.370 --> 02:52.573
INVESTMENT STUFF.
CAN I WEAR MY ‐‐

02:52.573 --> 02:54.254
ANYBODY NEEDS ME,
I'LL JUST...

02:54.254 --> 02:56.456
CAN I WEAR...
JUST GIVE ME A SHOUT.

02:56.456 --> 02:58.458
TEXT ME. TWEET ME.
I‐I ACTUALLY SMELLED YOU
MAKING THAT UP.

02:58.458 --> 03:00.300
I WILL. I WILL.
PUT THEM ON.
THERE'S A FIRE.

03:00.300 --> 03:01.662
HELP ME.
I WANT SEVEN BACK
IN A WEEK.

03:01.662 --> 03:03.063
LOOK, THERE'S AN EAGLE!

03:03.063 --> 03:04.545
CAN I WEAR MY SHIN GUARDS
TO SCHOOL?

03:04.545 --> 03:06.266
[ ALL TALKING ]
OKAY.

03:12.112 --> 03:13.113
HEY.

03:13.113 --> 03:15.355
OOH! ALL RIGHT ‐‐
SHOWER POLICE!

03:15.355 --> 03:16.837
MA'AM,
YOU WANT TO STEP INSIDE?

03:16.837 --> 03:19.079
THE WORD IS, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
WASHING YOUR BOOBS VERY WELL.

03:19.079 --> 03:20.841
NO, I'M NOT HERE
FOR SHOWER POLICE.

03:20.841 --> 03:21.922
HAD TO GIVE IT A TRY ‐‐

03:21.922 --> 03:23.684
MISS 100% OF THE SHOTS
YOU NEVER TAKE.

03:23.684 --> 03:24.805
WHAT'S UP?

03:24.805 --> 03:26.486
JUST FEELING A LITTLE
UN‐NEEDED LATELY.

03:26.486 --> 03:28.128
WELL, THE SHOWER POLICE
NEED YOU.

03:28.128 --> 03:29.449
BY THE KIDS.
I SEE.

03:29.449 --> 03:32.052
WE'RE HAVING A REAL CONVERSATION
ABOUT REAL THINGS.

03:32.052 --> 03:34.334
[ WATER TURNS OFF ]
WHAT'S UP?

03:34.334 --> 03:36.577
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN LIVING HERE
FOR ALMOST A YEAR

03:36.577 --> 03:37.898
AND I JUST FEEL LIKE I'M...

03:37.898 --> 03:39.900
MORE OF A ROOMMATE
THAN A PARENT.

03:39.900 --> 03:41.502
LIKE SOME WEIRD
CRAIGSLIST ROOMMATE

03:41.502 --> 03:43.103
THAT EVERYONE
POLITELY IGNORES.

03:43.103 --> 03:44.464
OH, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

03:44.464 --> 03:45.586
HILLARY'S RUDE TO YOU
SOMETIMES.

03:45.586 --> 03:46.827
I JUST FEEL LIKE
YOU JUST DO EVERYTHING

03:46.827 --> 03:48.468
AND THEN THERE'S NOTHING LEFT
FOR ME TO DO.

03:48.468 --> 03:50.070
WHY SHOULD YOU HAVE TO
DEAL WITH MY STUFF?

03:50.070 --> 03:53.113
IT'S MY JOB. I'M THEIR DAD.
I'M THE CRAP‐MASTER.

03:53.113 --> 03:55.115
BUT I COULD BE
ASSISTANT CRAP‐MASTER.

03:55.115 --> 03:57.077
YOU WANT MORE CRAP?
I'LL GIVE YOU MORE CRAP.
YES.

03:57.077 --> 03:58.438
ALL I WANT IS MORE CRAP.

03:58.438 --> 04:02.923
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

04:02.923 --> 04:04.525
ALL RIGHT!
[ WHISTLES ]

04:04.525 --> 04:07.167
KILLER BEES, HUDDLE UP.
BRING IT IN! BRING IT IN!

04:07.167 --> 04:09.169
LOT OF GOOD STUFF TODAY.

04:09.169 --> 04:10.450
GREAT SPIRIT.

04:10.450 --> 04:11.532
YEAH!
YEAH!
YEAH!
YEAH!

04:11.532 --> 04:13.453
YOU GUYS ‐‐
YOU GUYS LOVE TO CHEER.

04:13.453 --> 04:15.255
UH, COUPLE OF THINGS
TO THINK ABOUT ‐‐

04:15.255 --> 04:18.458
IN GENERAL, LET'S ‐‐
LET'S MAKE IT A GOAL

04:18.458 --> 04:22.102
TO NOT SIT DOWN AS MUCH
DURING A SCRIMMAGE.

04:22.102 --> 04:23.944
YAY!
YAY!
YAY!
YAY!

04:23.944 --> 04:25.946
ALSO, UH,
GO TO THE BATHROOM ‐‐

04:25.946 --> 04:29.910
VERY IMPORTANT ‐‐
<i>BEFORE</i> PRACTICE, OKAY?

04:29.910 --> 04:32.112
AND, IAN, IF YOU DO
NEED TO GO DURING PRACTICE,

04:32.112 --> 04:34.915
JUST, PLEASE,
LEAVE THE FIELD, OKAY?

04:34.915 --> 04:36.917
COACH DUANE,
ANYTHING YOU WANT TO ADD?

04:36.917 --> 04:39.600
I THINK MY WIFE IS HAVING
AN AFFAIR WITH MY BROTHER.

04:39.600 --> 04:41.201
YAY!
YAY!
YAY!
YAY!

04:41.201 --> 04:43.644
ALL RIGHT.
UH, BRING IT IN.

04:43.644 --> 04:45.646
ALL: BUZZ, BUZZ, BUZZ, BUZZ,
BUZZ, BUZZ, BUZZ, BUZZ, BUZZ!

04:45.646 --> 04:47.287
ALL RIGHT.

04:47.287 --> 04:51.091
HEY, UH, MAYBE A LITTLE LESS
SHARING WITH THE KIDS.

04:51.091 --> 04:54.855
LOOK AT YOU ‐‐
DOING STUFF.

04:54.855 --> 04:56.777
[ CHUCKLING ] YEAH.
IT'S EXCITING, RIGHT?
YEAH.

04:56.777 --> 04:58.579
YOU KNOW, HALF THESE KIDS
CAN'T EAT PEANUTS,

04:58.579 --> 05:00.060
AND THE OTHER HALF
ONLY EAT PEANUTS,

05:00.060 --> 05:03.023
SO, ONE WRONG BITE,
HALF THE TEAM DIES.

05:03.023 --> 05:05.065
OH, IT'S JUST
ORANGE SLICES AND WATER.

05:05.065 --> 05:06.867
W‐WELL, THERE'S ONE KID
WHO CAN'T HAVE ORANGES.

05:06.867 --> 05:09.069
HIS PARENTS HAVE SOME ISSUES
WITH FLORIDA.

05:09.069 --> 05:11.191
AND THAT KID
WITH THE SHORTY‐SHORTS

05:11.191 --> 05:13.954
CAN'T HAVE ANY WATER,
'CAUSE HE'S OVERHYDRATED.

05:14.715 --> 05:15.916
HEY, PETE?

05:15.916 --> 05:18.118
STAY STRONG, MAN.
YEAH?

05:18.118 --> 05:19.199
COME HERE.

05:19.199 --> 05:20.801
WHAT'S UP?

05:20.801 --> 05:22.042
CAN YOU KEEP BERT TONIGHT?

05:22.042 --> 05:24.084
'CAUSE MY TAI CHI CLASS
IS DOING A PUB CRAWL.

05:24.084 --> 05:26.607
UH, I COULD,
BUT I GOT A CLIENT DINNER.

05:26.607 --> 05:29.169
I'M NOT GONNA BE BACK UNTIL
WAY AFTER HIS BEDTIME.
PETE...

05:29.169 --> 05:30.490
I CAN PUT HIM TO BED.

05:30.490 --> 05:32.693
[ SCOFFS ]

05:32.693 --> 05:34.014
I SAW THAT LOOK.

05:34.014 --> 05:36.256
I CAN'T EVEN HAVE A LOOK?
COME ON. I CAN DO IT.

05:36.256 --> 05:39.099
I MEAN, I'VE SEEN PETE PUT HIM
TO BED A THOUSAND TIMES.

05:39.099 --> 05:41.141
I'VE BEEN TO THE ATM
LIKE A THOUSAND TIMES.

05:41.141 --> 05:43.223
DOESN'T MEAN I HAVE A CLUE
WHAT'S IN MY BANK ACCOUNT.

05:43.223 --> 05:45.666
I THINK ONE OF US
SHOULD STAY HOME.

05:45.666 --> 05:46.747
IS IT GONNA BE YOU
OR IS IT GONNA BE ME?

05:46.747 --> 05:48.068
IS IT AN IMPORTANT CLIENT?

05:48.068 --> 05:49.710
OOH ‐‐ IS IT GONNA
AFFECT MY ALIMONY?

05:49.710 --> 05:51.071
JACKIE, KATE'S RIGHT.

05:51.071 --> 05:52.833
SHE WANTS TO DO IT,
SHE CAN DO IT.

05:54.234 --> 05:57.077
WHAT WAS THAT LOOK?

05:57.077 --> 05:59.079
THAT WAS A WEIRD LOOK.
FROM NOW ON, NEW RULE ‐‐

05:59.079 --> 06:01.081
EVERYONE SAYS EVERYTHING
OUT LOUD.

06:02.603 --> 06:07.127
[ <i>TV CHATTER</i> ]

06:07.127 --> 06:09.089
WARREN, I WANT TO WATCH TV,
OKAY? MOVE YOUR FEET.

06:09.089 --> 06:10.691
HEY!
NO EATING ON THE COUCH!

06:10.691 --> 06:12.292
WHEN MOM'S NOT HERE,
I EAT WHERE I WANT.

06:12.292 --> 06:15.375
NOW MOVE YOUR GROSS FEET.
GROSS FEET?
THAT WAS VERY MEAN.

06:15.375 --> 06:18.058
APOLOGIZE TO MY FEET.
NEVER.

06:18.058 --> 06:20.621
OKAY, THEN I'M JUST GONNA
HAVE TO TAKE YOUR SNACKS.

06:20.621 --> 06:22.543
FEET! CONFISCATE SNACKS!

06:22.543 --> 06:24.184
FOOT SNACKS!
JERK, GET YOUR FEET
OFF MY SALSA!

06:24.184 --> 06:25.746
[ GRUNTS ]
[ GASPS ]

06:25.746 --> 06:28.589
OH, MY GOD.

06:28.589 --> 06:29.790
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

06:29.790 --> 06:31.431
WHAT'S UP, STUDLY?
WARREN: DAD, UH...

06:31.431 --> 06:33.994
ME AND HILLARY SPILLED SALSA
ON MOM'S WHITE COUCH.

06:33.994 --> 06:36.997
[ LAUGHS ]
OOH! OOH‐OOH‐OOH!

06:36.997 --> 06:38.799
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
WHAT DO WE DO?

06:38.799 --> 06:40.000
[ LAUGHS ]

06:40.000 --> 06:43.163
[ SCOFFS ] DAD?
BE SERIOUS, OKAY?

06:43.163 --> 06:44.885
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO?

06:44.885 --> 06:45.966
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.

06:45.966 --> 06:47.087
YOU'RE CALLING YOUR FATHER
FOR ADVICE.

06:47.087 --> 06:49.970
HERE'S MY ADVICE ‐‐
RUN AWAY.

06:49.970 --> 06:50.971
[ SCOFFS ]

06:50.971 --> 06:52.132
[ CLICK ]

06:52.132 --> 06:53.093
HELLO?

06:53.093 --> 06:55.616
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
POOR KIDS.

06:55.616 --> 06:56.857
WE'RE SCREWED.
[ SIGHS ]

06:56.857 --> 06:59.179
MOM LOVES TO PUNISH US
IN THOSE TWISTED WAYS.

06:59.179 --> 07:00.501
I KNOW ‐‐ A‐AND REMEMBER
THAT ONE TIME

07:00.501 --> 07:01.822
I WOULDN'T STOP
PICKING MY NOSE

07:01.822 --> 07:03.984
AND SO SHE ‐‐ SHE PUT THAT
DOG CONE COLLAR ON ME?

07:03.984 --> 07:05.345
SHE CANNOT FIND OUT
ABOUT THIS.

07:05.345 --> 07:07.788
WAIT. WAIT.

07:07.788 --> 07:09.550
SHE WON'T!

07:11.271 --> 07:13.714
OH, MY GOD!

07:16.637 --> 07:19.359
OH! CHECK IT!
GENIUS.

07:19.359 --> 07:21.802
OKAY, AS LONG AS WE KEEP
A UNITED FRONT, WE'LL BE FINE.

07:21.802 --> 07:22.963
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
HEY, GUYS.

07:22.963 --> 07:25.165
HEY, MOM!
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

07:25.165 --> 07:26.486
IT WAS GREAT.

07:26.486 --> 07:27.888
HEY, HILLARY.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

07:27.888 --> 07:29.570
BYE, MOM!
BYE, MOM! [ CHUCKLES ]

07:35.896 --> 07:37.257
"'I'M NOT AFRAID
OF YOUR BREATH,'

07:37.257 --> 07:39.780
"AND HE GAVE THE DRAGON
A KISS.

07:39.780 --> 07:44.184
AND THAT'S HOW THE DRAGON
LEARNED TO LOVE."

07:44.184 --> 07:46.226
OKEYDOKEY.

07:46.226 --> 07:47.988
WE'VE GOT YOUR WATER ‐‐
CHECK.

07:47.988 --> 07:50.591
MR. BEAR'S WATER ‐‐ CHECK.

07:50.591 --> 07:52.873
I SEE YOU'VE MADE SOME CHANGES
TO YOUR WARDROBE FOR THE WEEK,

07:52.873 --> 07:54.234
WHICH I TOTALLY RESPECT.

07:54.234 --> 07:57.037
AND NOW IT'S TIME

07:57.037 --> 07:59.600
TO CLOSE YOUR EYES
AND GO TO SLEEP.

07:59.600 --> 08:02.082
AND I'LL COUNT YOU DOWN
FROM 10.

08:02.082 --> 08:04.204
HOW ABOUT
FROM A BILLION?

08:05.926 --> 08:07.528
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO COUNT
THAT HIGH.

08:07.528 --> 08:09.970
HOW ABOUT
FROM A MILLION?

08:11.211 --> 08:13.614
OKAY.

08:13.614 --> 08:16.016
A MILLION...

08:19.339 --> 08:21.061
HI.

08:21.061 --> 08:23.864
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

08:36.597 --> 08:37.958
[ PANTING ]

08:37.958 --> 08:40.200
[ SIGHS ]

08:40.881 --> 08:43.604
[ RUSTLING ]

08:45.245 --> 08:48.088
BERT?
HI!
ARE WE PLAYING A GAME?

08:48.088 --> 08:49.209
NO.

08:50.090 --> 08:51.692
I'M STILL AWAKE.

08:51.692 --> 08:54.054
WHY?

08:54.054 --> 08:55.696
DIANE: HEY, GUYS.
SNACK'S READY.

08:55.696 --> 08:56.897
JUST ACT COOL.

08:56.897 --> 08:58.258
I ALWAYS DO.

08:58.258 --> 09:00.781
OH, MOM,
YOU LOOK RAVISHING.

09:00.781 --> 09:02.422
OH. WHY, THANK YOU,
SWEETHEART.

09:02.422 --> 09:06.426
OKAY, GUYS, DIG IN.
I MADE QUESADILLAS.

09:06.426 --> 09:08.188
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:08.188 --> 09:10.030
OKAY.

09:10.030 --> 09:12.032
ANY OTHER TOPPING
SUGGESTIONS?

09:12.032 --> 09:14.595
S‐SOUR ‐‐ SOUR CREAM.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:14.595 --> 09:15.796
CHOCOLATE.

09:15.796 --> 09:16.997
RELISH.

09:16.997 --> 09:18.438
UH, MUSTARD?

09:18.438 --> 09:20.160
[ GROANS ]

09:20.160 --> 09:22.202
RELISH.

09:22.202 --> 09:26.406
I WAS THINKING OF SOMETHING
JUST A LITTLE MORE <i>PICANTE.</i>

09:26.406 --> 09:29.289
I KNOW ‐‐
HOW ABOUT SOME SALSA?

09:29.289 --> 09:31.051
OH, YEAH. SALSA ‐‐ RIGHT.
SALSA.

09:31.051 --> 09:33.814
WE HAVEN'T HAD SALSA
IN A WHILE. RIGHT, HIL?

09:33.814 --> 09:34.815
THAT'S RIGHT, WARREN.

09:34.815 --> 09:37.377
AAH. NEW BOTTLE.

09:37.377 --> 09:39.139
DIG.

09:39.139 --> 09:41.301
ALL RIGHT. OH!

09:41.301 --> 09:43.143
I ALMOST FORGOT ‐‐
NAPKINS,

09:43.143 --> 09:44.505
JUST IN CASE ONE OF US
SPILLS THE SALSA.

09:44.505 --> 09:45.786
[ CHUCKLES ]
RIGHT.

09:45.786 --> 09:48.028
SHE KNOWS. SHE NEVER TALKS
THIS MUCH ABOUT SALSA.

09:48.028 --> 09:49.189
MAYBE SHE TALKS ABOUT SALSA
ALL THE TIME,

09:49.189 --> 09:51.111
BUT WE'RE JUST
NOTICING IT NOW.
WHAT?!

09:53.794 --> 09:55.195
HEY, DIG IN GUYS.

09:55.195 --> 09:56.476
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

09:58.318 --> 09:59.520
MMM.

09:59.520 --> 10:02.002
THE SALSA IS
WHAT MAKES IT SO GOOD.

10:02.002 --> 10:04.084
MMM.

10:04.084 --> 10:06.126
KATE: IT'S BEEN THREE HOURS.
WE'RE BUDDIES, RIGHT?

10:06.126 --> 10:07.127
I LIKE YOU!

10:07.127 --> 10:08.248
OKAY, GOOD.
I LIKE YOU, TOO.

10:08.248 --> 10:10.210
NOW CAN YOU JUST
PLEASE TELL ME, BERTO.

10:10.210 --> 10:11.291
WHAT CAN I DO?

10:11.291 --> 10:12.973
SOMETIMES I LIKE
"THIS LITTLE PIGGY."

10:12.973 --> 10:14.655
GREAT. PERFECT.

10:17.177 --> 10:18.819
THIS LITTLE PIGGY
WENT TO MARKET.
[ LAUGHING ]

10:18.819 --> 10:21.261
AND THIS LITTLE
PIGGY STAYED HOME.

10:21.261 --> 10:24.865
AND THIS LITTLE PIGGY...
WENT TO PILATES.

10:24.865 --> 10:28.949
AND THIS LITTLE PIGGY WAS LIKE,
"BERT, GO TO SLEEP!"

10:28.949 --> 10:30.230
THAT WAS ALL WRONG.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.312
I'M EVEN MORE AWAKE NOW.

10:32.312 --> 10:33.514
[ GROANS ]

10:37.197 --> 10:38.438
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

10:38.438 --> 10:40.080
TONIGHT, YOU'RE GONNA
FALL ASLEEP LIKE I DID

10:40.080 --> 10:41.922
WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE.

10:43.083 --> 10:46.046
I NEVER GET TO WATCH TV
IN BED!

10:46.046 --> 10:48.008
I KNOW. IT'LL BE
OUR LITTLE SECRET, OKAY?

10:48.008 --> 10:49.409
LET'S PINKY SWEAR!

10:49.409 --> 10:51.532
I LIKE THE WAY YOU ROLL.

10:51.532 --> 10:53.133
ALL RIGHT.

10:53.133 --> 10:54.535
MAN: <i>TEMPERATURES IN THE SOUTH</i>
<i>WILL BE</i>

10:54.535 --> 10:56.256
<i>DROPPING BY TOMORROW NIGHT.</i>
[ SIGHS ]

10:56.256 --> 10:58.418
<i>IN SPORTS,</i>
<i>LOS ANGELES BEAT SAN FRANCISCO</i>

10:58.418 --> 11:00.060
<i>TO STAY ALIVE</i>
<i>IN THE CHASE FOR THE WEST,</i>

11:00.060 --> 11:02.062
<i>AND SEATTLE LOST TO TEXAS</i>

11:02.062 --> 11:04.104
<i>DESPITE HERNANDEZ</i>
<i>GOING EIGHT INNINGS...</i>

11:04.104 --> 11:06.707
<i>THAT'S ALL</i>
<i>FOR THE NIGHTLY NEWS AT 11.</i>

11:06.707 --> 11:09.670
<i>FROM OUR FAMILY TO YOURS,</i>
<i>GOOD NIGHT.</i>

11:09.670 --> 11:11.872
ANNOUNCER:
<i>TONIGHT, ON "COLD FILE"...</i>

11:11.872 --> 11:13.674
<i>MARK STYMAN</i>
<i>WAS A BRILLIANT SURGEON,</i>

11:13.674 --> 11:16.957
<i>BUT THIS SURGEON HAD A SECRET.</i>

11:16.957 --> 11:20.881
<i>DR. MARK STYMAN</i>
<i>LIKED TO STEAL UTERUSES.</i>

11:25.566 --> 11:26.727
HEY, BUDDY.
ALL RIGHT, TIME TO GET UP.

11:26.727 --> 11:28.729
THE KILLER BEES
NEED THEIR GOALIE.

11:28.729 --> 11:29.970
I'M AN ALL‐STAR.

11:29.970 --> 11:32.533
OKAY, RIGHT ‐‐
EVERYBODY'S AN ALL‐STAR.

11:32.533 --> 11:34.374
UP. COME ON.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

11:34.374 --> 11:36.897
OH, I'M TIRED.
I SLEPT BAD.

11:36.897 --> 11:38.258
SHH!
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

11:38.258 --> 11:40.180
DON'T SAY THAT...
TO YOUR DAD.

11:40.180 --> 11:42.262
KATE, COULD A DOCTOR
STEAL MY UTERUS?

11:42.262 --> 11:45.706
STEAL YOUR UTERUS?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

11:45.706 --> 11:47.107
I SAW IT ON "COLD FILE"

11:47.107 --> 11:49.469
LAST NIGHT
AFTER YOU FELL ASLEEP.

11:49.469 --> 11:50.711
OOH, BOY.

11:51.832 --> 11:53.954
OKAY, LISTEN, LET'S JUST
KEEP IT BETWEEN US

11:53.954 --> 11:55.395
WITH A PINKY SWEAR?

11:55.395 --> 11:56.717
OKAY.

11:56.717 --> 11:57.718
OKAY. GOOD.

11:57.718 --> 11:59.119
PETE:
HEY, BERT! WE GOT TO GO!

12:00.120 --> 12:02.002
HEY.

12:02.002 --> 12:04.364
JUST THIS ONCE, YOU CAN HAVE
A SIP OF MY COFFEE.

12:04.364 --> 12:06.326
IT'LL WAKE YOU UP.
THANKS.

12:06.326 --> 12:08.929
[ SUCKING ]

12:10.971 --> 12:13.534
[ SLURPING ]

12:13.534 --> 12:16.376
[ GASPS ]
I FEEL BETTER ALREADY.

12:16.376 --> 12:18.338
OH, BERT.

12:18.338 --> 12:21.141
OKAY.
ONE LAST PINKY SWEAR.

12:22.062 --> 12:24.264
HEY, BERT!
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

12:24.264 --> 12:25.506
YEAH, HE'S COMING.

12:25.506 --> 12:28.108
YOU KNOW HOW KIDS GET
SOMETIMES IN THE MORNING.

12:28.108 --> 12:29.469
I WAS THINKING ABOUT
WHAT YOU SAID YESTERDAY

12:29.469 --> 12:30.631
ABOUT WANTING TO BE
MORE INVOLVED.

12:30.631 --> 12:32.913
YOU GOT BERT TO SLEEP
LAST NIGHT.

12:32.913 --> 12:35.596
I THINK YOU'RE READY
FOR YOUR NEXT CHALLENGE.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

12:35.596 --> 12:36.837
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO ASSISTANT COACH

12:36.837 --> 12:39.039
THE LOSINGEST TEAM
IN LEAGUE HISTORY?

12:39.039 --> 12:40.601
OH, PETE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:40.601 --> 12:42.162
I THINK
I'M ALREADY DOING SO M‐‐

12:42.162 --> 12:44.164
DON'T WORRY.
YOU'RE GONNA HATE IT.

12:44.164 --> 12:46.527
[ SMOOCHES ]
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

12:46.527 --> 12:47.768
WHAT HAPPENED
TO COACH DUANE?

12:47.768 --> 12:49.970
UH, HE HAD
A NERVOUS BREAKDOWN.

12:49.970 --> 12:52.853
ALL RIGHT!
LET'S DO THIS!

12:52.853 --> 12:54.615
SOMEONE GOT
A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

12:54.615 --> 12:56.056
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:56.056 --> 12:57.938
YEP. LET'S GO.
[ BLOWS WHISTLE ]

12:57.938 --> 12:59.379
[ LATIN AMERICAN MUSIC PLAYS ]

13:01.141 --> 13:03.664
AH, COME DANCE
WITH ME, GUYS!

13:03.664 --> 13:06.066
[ ROLLS TONGUE ]
COME ON, HIL!

13:06.066 --> 13:08.068
[ HUMMING ]
COME ON.

13:08.068 --> 13:09.910
ALL RIGHT, GET READY
TO MOVE YOUR HIPS.

13:11.271 --> 13:14.314
MM!
WHAT IS THIS MUSIC?

13:14.314 --> 13:15.556
IT'S CALLED...

13:15.556 --> 13:17.237
SALSA.

13:17.237 --> 13:20.000
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

13:20.000 --> 13:22.883
OH, MY GOD.

13:22.883 --> 13:24.044
WARREN.

13:26.126 --> 13:27.968
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:27.968 --> 13:29.329
HOW DID IT GO WITH BERT
LAST NIGHT?

13:29.329 --> 13:30.330
DID HE SAY ANYTHING?

13:30.330 --> 13:31.331
NOPE.

13:31.331 --> 13:33.053
OH, IT WENT GREAT.
OH, GOOD.

13:33.053 --> 13:34.575
I'M SO HUNG OVER.

13:34.575 --> 13:37.698
THOSE TAI CHI LADIES ARE
SURPRISINGLY VIOLENT DRINKERS.
OH.

13:37.698 --> 13:39.219
PETE: BRING IT IN!
BRING IT IN, BEES!
AH!

13:39.219 --> 13:40.861
GOT TO GO ‐‐ NEW COACH.

13:40.861 --> 13:43.103
OH, YEAH? OH, GOOD LUCK.
OH, THANKS.

13:43.103 --> 13:44.625
HEY, YOU KNOW, I COACHED
THE ZEBRAS TWO YEARS AGO.

13:44.625 --> 13:48.028
IT WAS A MESS. THEY KEPT
KICKING IT OUT TO THE REFS.
GREAT.

13:48.028 --> 13:51.431
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY ABOUT
HUSBAND/WIFE COACHING TEAMS.

13:51.431 --> 13:52.753
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

13:52.753 --> 13:54.234
PETE: GATHER 'ROUND,
GATHER 'ROUND, HUDDLE UP.

13:54.234 --> 13:57.638
SPECIAL DAY ‐‐ I WANT TO
INTRODUCE YOU TO COACH KATE

13:57.638 --> 13:58.959
SHE LIVES IN OUR HOUSE!

13:58.959 --> 14:00.841
SHE'S GONNA BE HELPING US
WHILE COACH DUANE

14:00.841 --> 14:03.163
GETS THE HELP
THAT HE SO DESPERATELY NEEDS.

14:03.163 --> 14:05.686
HI, GUYS.
I'M SUPER EXCITED TO BE HERE.

14:05.686 --> 14:07.127
I‐I LOVE SOCCER,

14:07.127 --> 14:08.969
AND I LOVE PLAYING
WITH LITTLE BOYS.
BERT.

14:08.969 --> 14:10.330
AND...PLAYING
WITH LITTLE GIRLS...AS WELL.

14:10.330 --> 14:13.013
GUYS, LET'S GIVE HER
A BIG BEES WELCOME.

14:13.013 --> 14:13.974
BUZZ!
BUZZ!
BUZZ!
BUZZ!

14:13.974 --> 14:15.135
I'M THE SUN!

14:15.135 --> 14:17.337
BERT?
I'M THE MOON!

14:17.337 --> 14:18.739
I'M CHRISTMAS!

14:18.739 --> 14:20.140
BERT, YOU WANT TO ‐‐
YOU WANT TO BRING IT IN?

14:20.140 --> 14:21.742
HE'S EXCITED.
REIN IT DOWN A LITTLE BIT.

14:21.742 --> 14:22.983
OKAY, UH,
LIKE I WAS SAYING ‐‐

14:22.983 --> 14:25.065
COACH KATE IS GONNA BE
A VALUABLE ADDITION.

14:25.065 --> 14:26.466
PAIR UP, GET A BALL.

14:26.466 --> 14:28.428
WILL YOU CHECK ON BERT?
HE SEEMS A LITTLE WEIRD.
YEAH.

14:28.428 --> 14:30.390
NO, NO ‐‐ PROBABLY JUST EXCITED
THAT I'M COACHING.

14:30.390 --> 14:32.032
OKAY.
I GOT IT.

14:32.032 --> 14:33.193
HEY, BERT.
HEY, BERT. HEY!

14:33.193 --> 14:35.435
GET OVER HERE. GET OVER HERE.
COME HERE.

14:35.435 --> 14:36.717
OKAY, LISTEN ‐‐

14:36.717 --> 14:38.639
I NEED YOU
TO TONE IT DOWN A NOTCH.

14:38.639 --> 14:40.040
I CAN TASTE MY TEETH!

14:40.040 --> 14:41.441
[ LAUGHS ]
OKAY. SHH!
DON'T SAY THAT.

14:41.441 --> 14:43.684
OKAY, THAT'S ‐‐
THAT'S GREAT. JUST WALK.

14:45.045 --> 14:46.166
YES, MA'AM.

14:51.371 --> 14:54.134
WHY DID YOU AND MOM NEED TO HAVE
A PRIVATE CONVERSATION?

14:54.134 --> 14:56.416
SHE SAID IF I WAS GOING TO ‐‐
TO PEE IN HER BATHROOM,

14:56.416 --> 14:58.018
THAT I HAD TO SIT DOWN.

14:58.018 --> 14:59.700
SHE'S GETTING TO ME.

14:59.700 --> 15:02.302
OKAY, SHE'S GETTING
INSIDE MY HEAD!

15:02.302 --> 15:03.784
MAYBE I SHOULD JUST CONFESS.

15:03.784 --> 15:04.825
NO, DON'T ‐‐
LOOK, UNITED FRONT.

15:04.825 --> 15:06.146
WE'RE GONNA BE
AT DAD'S TOMORROW.

15:06.146 --> 15:08.228
YOU CAN MAKE IT
UNTIL THEN.

15:08.228 --> 15:12.833
DIANE: HILLARY, I NEED TO
SPEAK TO YOU PRIVATELY.

15:12.833 --> 15:14.715
[ SWEETLY ]
COMING, MOTHER.

15:17.838 --> 15:18.959
[ GROANS ]

15:21.441 --> 15:23.163
[ YAWNS ]

15:25.646 --> 15:27.007
[ GROANS ]

15:30.410 --> 15:32.092
[ GROANS ]

15:34.254 --> 15:37.177
REMEMBER, YOU ‐‐ YOU'RE TRYING
TO KEEP THEM OUT OF THERE.
OH, MAN.

15:37.177 --> 15:39.700
PICK UP.
IT'S YOUR HOUSE.
NOBODY COMES IN.

15:40.821 --> 15:44.064
HEY, BUD, YOU WANT TO
TRY SOME STANDING UP?

15:44.064 --> 15:45.586
I NEED COFFEE.

15:45.586 --> 15:47.027
HA!
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,

15:47.027 --> 15:48.388
HE'LL BE ASKING FOR
<i>THE WALL STREET JOURNAL</i>

15:48.388 --> 15:49.950
AND A CHEESE DANISH.

15:49.950 --> 15:51.351
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH THE BERTSTER?

15:51.351 --> 15:54.955
I DON'T KNOW. DID HE EAT
SOMETHING WEIRD LAST NIGHT?

15:54.955 --> 15:56.196
NO, GUYS,
I THINK HE'S FINE.

15:56.196 --> 15:58.038
YOU KNOW, LET'S ‐‐
LET'S GET UP, BERT,

15:58.038 --> 16:00.000
AND SHOW 'EM WHAT YOU GOT,
ALL RIGHT?

16:00.000 --> 16:02.402
COME ON. HERE WE GO.
UP YOU GO. ON YOUR FEET.

16:02.402 --> 16:04.605
YOU GOT IT, BUD.
GET UP, BUD.
YOU READY? HERE WE GO.
YOU GOT IT, BUDDY.

16:04.605 --> 16:06.006
READY? READY?
HERE WE GO.

16:06.006 --> 16:08.128
YEAH!
THERE'S MY ALL‐STAR!

16:08.128 --> 16:09.970
ALL RIGHT,
YOU READY FOR ANOTHER ONE?

16:09.970 --> 16:12.052
NOW, PICK UP THE ENERGY.
PICK UP THE ENERGY.

16:12.052 --> 16:14.454
HANDS UP!
LET'S GO! LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

16:14.454 --> 16:15.455
HANDS UP! LET'S GO!
LET'S GO!

16:16.176 --> 16:19.179
OW! MY UTERUS!

16:21.381 --> 16:22.583
PETE: OW!
OHH!

16:22.583 --> 16:24.024
MY ‐‐ MY BABY.
OH, MY GOD.

16:24.024 --> 16:25.586
HE BLOCKED IT!

16:28.148 --> 16:29.109
OH, BERT.

16:32.753 --> 16:34.354
YOU GUYS,
I FEEL TERRIBLE.

16:34.354 --> 16:36.036
I AM SO SORRY.

16:36.036 --> 16:37.437
YEAH, "SORRY" ISN'T GONNA
REDUCE THE SWELLING

16:37.437 --> 16:38.759
IN MY SON'S TESTICLE.

16:38.759 --> 16:40.761
YOU ACT LIKE
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING, KATE,

16:40.761 --> 16:42.603
AND YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING.

16:42.603 --> 16:45.526
YOU KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT...ANYTHING.

16:46.406 --> 16:48.248
SO, I'M GONNA
TELL YOU SOMETHING ‐‐

16:48.248 --> 16:51.371
JACKIE, KATE KNOWS
THAT SHE SCREWED UP.

16:51.371 --> 16:53.413
YEAH ‐‐ NO ‐‐
<i>YOU</i> SCREWED UP.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.415
YOU ‐‐ I HOPE YOU CAN
STILL BE A GRANDPA

16:55.415 --> 16:58.418
AFTER ALL OF BERT'S...
THIS.

16:58.418 --> 17:01.101
I THINK BERT'S "THIS"
WILL BE FINE.

17:01.101 --> 17:02.663
I JUST WANTED TO DO SOMETHING
TO HELP, YOU KNOW?

17:02.663 --> 17:04.104
I JUST WANTED TO BE
PART OF THE FAMILY,

17:04.104 --> 17:06.587
AND PETE GAVE ME THE CHANCE,
AND I JUST ‐‐ I BLEW IT.

17:06.587 --> 17:09.229
YEAH, YOU DID, LIKE...
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

17:09.229 --> 17:11.031
"NO!"
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

17:11.031 --> 17:12.673
YEAH ‐‐ REAL BAD.
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I AM JUST ‐‐

17:12.673 --> 17:14.474
I'M GONNA GO TO THE CAFETERIA
AND GET SOMETHING.

17:14.474 --> 17:16.517
DO YOU WANT ANYTHING?
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

17:16.517 --> 17:19.039
I BET THAT BERT WOULD JUST LOVE
A TRIPLE ESPRESSO.

17:19.039 --> 17:22.402
YOU KNOW, I HAVE SAID IT ONCE,
AND I WILL SAY IT AGAIN ‐‐

17:22.402 --> 17:25.485
ASIDE FROM ME, I DO NOT
UNDERSTAND YOUR TASTE IN WOMEN.

17:25.485 --> 17:28.288
I THINK YOU NEED
TO CUT HER SOME SLACK.

17:28.288 --> 17:30.490
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU REMEMBER
WHEN WE GOT MARRIED?

17:30.490 --> 17:33.694
BARELY.
THAT OPEN BAR WAS FANTASTIC.

17:33.694 --> 17:36.657
YOU REMEMBER HOW HARD
DIANE WAS ON YOU?

17:36.657 --> 17:39.660
YOU'RE ACTING LIKE DIANE.

17:39.660 --> 17:42.222
WHAT? LIKE SMART, NO‐NONSENSE,
VERY ACCOMPLISHED?

17:42.222 --> 17:43.584
OH, I GET IT.

17:43.584 --> 17:46.907
N‐NO, I MEAN, Y‐Y‐YOU'RE
BEING HARD ON KATE.

17:46.907 --> 17:51.431
SHE'S ‐‐ SHE'S REALLY TRYING.
SHE LOVES OUR LITTLE GUY.

17:51.431 --> 17:54.675
MR. AND MRS. HARRISON,
YOU CAN SEE YOUR SON NOW.

17:54.675 --> 17:56.236
WE DON'T HAVE A SON.

17:57.558 --> 17:58.679
OH, HONEST MISTAKE.

17:58.679 --> 18:00.721
MR. AND MRS. HARRISON,
BERT IS FINE.

18:00.721 --> 18:01.722
YOU CAN SEE HIM NOW.
[ GASPS ]

18:01.722 --> 18:02.723
GREAT.
YES!

18:02.723 --> 18:03.804
DO ‐‐ GIVE HIM A TIP.

18:03.804 --> 18:05.445
HEY, HAVE YOU GUYS
SEEN MY PHONE?

18:05.445 --> 18:07.447
WARREN: NO.

18:07.447 --> 18:10.531
WARREN!

18:11.572 --> 18:13.694
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU DID THIS.

18:13.694 --> 18:16.496
OH, YEAH, I DID THAT,
'CAUSE I'M CRAZY.

18:16.496 --> 18:17.658
NO!

18:17.658 --> 18:19.099
OH, HEY, GUYS.

18:19.099 --> 18:20.180
DO YOU
WANT TO WATCH A MOVIE?

18:20.180 --> 18:22.583
I HAVE RENTED "LA BAMBA."

18:22.583 --> 18:26.186
OKAY! THAT'S ENOUGH!
PLEASE, STOP, OKAY?

18:26.186 --> 18:28.348
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST PUNISH US
LIKE A NORMAL PARENT?

18:28.348 --> 18:30.511
I WANTED TO TELL YOU
THE WHOLE TIME, I SWEAR!

18:31.752 --> 18:33.313
NORMAL PARENTS
DON'T GET RESULTS.

18:33.313 --> 18:36.116
ARE YOU EVER GOING TO EAT
ON THE SOFA AGAIN?
BOTH: NO!

18:36.116 --> 18:38.198
ARE YOU EVER GOING TO HIDE
ANYTHING FROM ME AGAIN?
BOTH: NO!

18:38.198 --> 18:39.800
DO YOU LOVE ME THE MOST?
NO!
YES!

18:39.800 --> 18:41.602
I ‐‐

18:41.602 --> 18:43.684
SORRY, I GOT CAUGHT UP
IN ALL THE NOS.

18:43.684 --> 18:45.125
YES, OF COURSE
I LOVE YOU THE MOST.

18:45.125 --> 18:47.127
OKAY.

18:47.127 --> 18:49.129
GIVE YOUR MOM A HUG.
AWW!

18:49.129 --> 18:50.691
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

18:50.691 --> 18:54.575
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:54.575 --> 18:57.578
YOU CAN [CLICKS TONGUE]
GO ON IN.

18:57.578 --> 18:59.499
OH, IT'S OKAY, JACKIE.
I DON'T NEED TO GO IN.

18:59.499 --> 19:02.062
LOOK, I KNOW
I GOT MAD TODAY.

19:02.062 --> 19:04.745
BUT DEEP DOWN HERE,
IN MY JACKIE HEART,

19:04.745 --> 19:07.588
I KNOW THAT IT'S NOT EASY
BEING A NEW STEPMOM.

19:07.588 --> 19:08.949
I GUESS WHAT I'M SAYING,
KATE, IS,

19:08.949 --> 19:10.751
WE'RE KIND OF THE SAME,
RIGHT?

19:10.751 --> 19:12.192
FREE SPIRITS ‐‐

19:12.192 --> 19:14.274
THE SOULS OF BIRDS
IN PEOPLE BODIES.

19:14.274 --> 19:16.276
OH, YEAH.

19:16.276 --> 19:18.198
WELL, T‐THANKS, JACKIE.
THAT'S REALLY SWEET.

19:18.198 --> 19:20.601
BUT YOU DON'T NEED TO
LET ME GO IN. IT'S OKAY.

19:20.601 --> 19:22.442
YEAH, WELL, I'M NOT...

19:22.442 --> 19:24.685
LETTING YOU DO ANYTHING,
'CAUSE HE WANTS YOU.

19:24.685 --> 19:26.446
HE DOES?
YEAH.

19:26.446 --> 19:28.448
OH. OKAY. GREAT.
WELL, THEN...

19:28.448 --> 19:30.450
CAN YOU JUST ‐‐ I'M ‐‐
I'LL JUST GO IN THEN.

19:30.450 --> 19:31.612
ALL RIGHT.

19:31.612 --> 19:34.454
KATE!

19:34.454 --> 19:35.616
HEY, BUDDY!

19:35.616 --> 19:38.579
OH, I'M SO SORRY...
ABOUT THAT.

19:38.579 --> 19:40.500
I'M SORRY I BROKE
THE PINKY SWEAR.

19:40.500 --> 19:42.863
OH, APOLOGY ACCEPTED.
I'M MORE SORRY.

19:42.863 --> 19:44.825
ACTUALLY, HE INVITED YOU HERE
FOR A VERY SPECIAL REASON.

19:44.825 --> 19:46.667
WILL YOU DO THE PIGGIES?

19:46.667 --> 19:47.868
MY PIGGIES?
YES!

19:47.868 --> 19:49.630
OF COURSE!

19:49.630 --> 19:51.191
THIS LITTLE PIGGY
WENT TO THE MARKET.

19:51.191 --> 19:52.793
[ LAUGHING ]
THIS LITTLE PIGGY
STAYED HOME.

19:52.793 --> 19:54.755
THIS LITTLE PIGGY
WENT TO THE HAMPTONS.

19:54.755 --> 19:57.037
AND THIS LITTLE PIGGY WAS,
LIKE, TOTALLY JEALOUS.

19:57.037 --> 19:58.999
AND THIS LITTLE PIGGY
WAS LIKE,

19:58.999 --> 20:01.321
"I DON'T CARE. I'M GONNA
GO GET A TONGUE PIERCING."

20:01.321 --> 20:02.803
[ LAUGHS ]
IT'S STILL SO WRONG.

20:02.803 --> 20:05.285
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:05.285 --> 20:08.288
AND I WANT TO APOLOGIZE
TO YOU,

20:08.288 --> 20:10.290
BECAUSE, UM, YOU KNOW,
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU

20:10.290 --> 20:11.652
THAT I WAS
MESSING EVERYTHING UP.

20:11.652 --> 20:13.053
THAT'S ALL RIGHT ‐‐
JUST, IN THE FUTURE,

20:13.053 --> 20:14.815
LET'S NOT KEEP THINGS
FROM EACH OTHER, OKAY?

20:14.815 --> 20:17.297
THAT'S WHAT
MY EX‐WIVES ARE FOR.
[ LAUGHS ]

20:17.297 --> 20:19.620
OH, KATE, IT TURNS OUT
I DIDN'T HURT MY UTERUS AT ALL.

20:19.620 --> 20:21.021
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU DON'T
HAVE A UTERUS.

20:21.021 --> 20:22.823
REMEMBER, BUDDY?
GIRLS DO.

20:22.823 --> 20:25.586
SO...WHAT'S IN MY BUTT?

20:25.586 --> 20:28.228
BUTT STUFF.
UH‐HUH.

20:28.228 --> 20:30.390
WELL, ACTUALLY, THERE'S
A LOT OF THINGS IN YOUR BUTT.

20:30.390 --> 20:32.793
YOU KNOW, IF YOU THINK
ABOUT IT, THERE'S ‐‐
BUTT STUFF.

20:33.754 --> 20:36.156
BUTT STUFF. YEAH.

20:39.279 --> 20:41.441
EXCUSE ME, SIR?

20:42.242 --> 20:43.283
SHOWER POLICE?

20:43.283 --> 20:45.125
WE GOT A REPORT
THERE'S A MAN

20:45.125 --> 20:46.527
FITTING YOUR
SEXY DESCRIPTION

20:46.527 --> 20:48.168
WHO'S BEEN HANGING OUT
IN THIS SHOWER.

20:48.168 --> 20:50.490
I'D LIKE TO COME IN
AND INVESTIGATE.

20:50.490 --> 20:51.732
OKAY!

20:54.134 --> 20:56.977
BERT: KATE!
I NEED SOME ORANGE JUICE!

